
Overview of verb abridge

The verb abridge has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) abridge, foreshorten, abbreviate, shorten, cut, contract, reduce -- (reduce in scope while retaining essential elements; "The manuscript must be shortened")
2. abridge -- (lessen, diminish, or curtail; "the new law might abridge our freedom of expression")
